results.title: Jollies
results.material_description: Single channel moving image, black and white and audio
results.brief_description: An intimate and sardonic work about being an adolescent in mid-American suburbia. From touching the genitals of boys in school to finally getting to kiss the girl she wants, this very funny and accomplished experimental work was filmed while the director was herself a teen.

results.title: If Every Girl Had a Diary
results.material_description: Single channel moving image, black and white and audio
results.brief_description: Sadie Benning’s video diaries form a unique record of the development of a young artist. Within the confines of her bedroom, she creates a dense experimental work about a teenagers search for sexual and non-conformist expression. ‘If Every Girl Had a Diary’ is an intimate insight into suburban malaise and alienation, as well as being a defiantly accomplished piece of video art.

results.title: Digital Diaries for Memory Grid Pods. Tape 2
results.brief_description:
Eleven anonymous individual stories by young secondary school students produced in-house for Memory Grid Digital Diaries.
Works produced from the digital diaires program collected at the discretion of the program coordiantors. all submissions are anonymous. The Digital Diary project asks a diverse range of young people to share a personal story as they connect memories by way of simple moving images. Participants in the workshops look at one ‘moment’ in their lives and, concentrating on the simplicity and power of that one moment in time, they create a ‘lo-fi’ video work that speaks to the mind and heart. The story is then burnt to a CD (or put onto VHS) for the participants to keep, and the monologues become part of a specially curated database which, with the participant’s permission, is later screened at the Australian Centre for the Moving Image at Federation Square.

results.brief_description: A collaboration between students from Natimuk Primary School and animation artists Dave Jones funded as part of the Arts Victoria Artists in Schools program. results.title: The Kingpins showreel 2000-2002
results.brief_description:
A young, Sydney-based drag-king outfit producing hilarious music videos parodying genres such as the ‘boy band’, and glam metal. Artists: Emma Price, Técha Noble, Katie Price and Angelica Mesiti. Compilation preview tape contains:
1. Men’s Club, 2001
2. Evil Dick, 2001
3. This is my Remix Baby, 2001
4. Pussy Whipped, 2000
5. Verses 2002.

results.title: Shaun Gladwell: excerpts from selected video works 2000-2002
results.brief_description:
Gladwell describes his installations as ‘speculations on political and poetic aspects of transformation within urban politics.’ (2004 Proposal)
Five Fragments:
1. Kickflipper: Fragments of a Ballet (2000-2001)
2. Sydney: A Guide to Recent Architecture )2000-2001)
3. Linework (2000-2001)
4. Cycles of Radical Will (Team Rivo) and (Hikaru) (2001)
5. Need for Speed (2000).
